HEADWORD: jackhammer
<hw>jackhammer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a hammer having a strong steel
cutting blade, driven by compressed air in multiple rapid strokes, and
used for cutting through pavement, concrete, or other hard
substances.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> air hammer, pneumatic hammer.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

